    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a6037e5_18a2c7a9",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/host/libs/libOpenglRender/FrameBuffer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 16
      },
      "lineNbr": 644,
      "author": {
        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-19T20:59:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The result of m_procOwnedColorBuffers[pid] is defined to be a multiset.  Looking at genHandle(...), which is the result returned by createColorBufferLocked, it seems like it\u0027s intended to produce a unique value each time.  If there were a collision, things would just break, as far as I can tell.\n\nSo maybe this can just be a set, rather than a multiset?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 644,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 644,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "792de10c0f43a56253dcb02a794f985e0a0e978d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a6037e5_e73d0a14",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/host/libs/libOpenglRender/FrameBuffer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 16
      },
      "lineNbr": 644,
      "author": {
        "id": 1087303
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-19T21:29:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The purpose of the multiset is not for creation, but for opening. The process will own a reference of the color buffer when it creates or opens the color buffer. And nothing prevents it from opening a color buffer multiple times.",
      "parentUuid": "6a6037e5_18a2c7a9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 644,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 644,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "792de10c0f43a56253dcb02a794f985e0a0e978d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a6037e5_f885b304",
